## 2. Why Visualization Matters

Consider this dataset:

| Study hours | Exam score |
| ----------: | ---------: |
|           1 |         45 |
|           2 |         52 |
|           3 |         60 |
|           4 |         67 |
|           5 |         76 |
|           6 |         84 |

Reading the table suggests that students who study more tend to score higher.

A chart makes that relationship easier to see:

```text
Exam score
90 |                         *
80 |                    *
70 |               *
60 |          *
50 |     *
40 | *
   +----------------------------
     1  2  3  4  5  6
           Study hours
```

Visualization helps us detect:

* Trends
* Relationships
* Outliers
* Missing values
* Class imbalance
* Incorrect values
* Distribution shapes
* Model performance

In machine learning, visualization is not decoration. It is part of data analysis and model evaluation.

