## 14. Mathematical Intuition: Relationships

A positive relationship looks like:

```text
y
|           *
|        *
|      *
|   *
| *
+------------- x
```

As (x) increases, (y) tends to increase.

A negative relationship looks like:

```text
y
| *
|   *
|      *
|        *
|           *
+------------- x
```

As (x) increases, (y) tends to decrease.

No clear relationship:

```text
y
|    *       *
| *      *
|       *   *
|  *  *
|          *
+------------- x
```

A scatter plot does not prove causation. It only displays an observed relationship.

