## 16. Histogram Mathematical Intuition

Suppose the scores are divided into these intervals:

```text
40–49
50–59
60–69
70–79
80–89
90–99
```

The histogram counts how many values fall into each interval.

For example:

```text
Interval    Count
40–49         1
50–59         3
60–69         4
70–79         4
80–89         3
90–99         2
```

The bar height represents frequency:

[
\text{Frequency}
================

\text{Number of observations in a bin}
]

