## 18. Why Training and Validation Curves Matter

Suppose training accuracy continues improving, while validation accuracy stops improving:

```text
Accuracy
1.0 |                   Training
0.9 |                /
0.8 |         Validation ----
0.7 |       /
0.6 |    /
    +------------------------
      1  2  3  4  5  Epoch
```

This may indicate overfitting.

The model is improving on training data but not on unseen validation data.

Visualization helps identify this problem quickly.

