## 21. Misleading Axis Example

Consider two values:

```text
Company A: 95
Company B: 97
```

If the y-axis begins at 0:

```text
100 |          *
 75 |    *
 50 |
 25 |
  0 +------------
```

The difference appears small.

If the y-axis begins at 94:

```text
98 |          *
97 |          *
96 |
95 |    *
94 +------------
```

The same difference appears dramatic.

Changing axis limits is not automatically wrong, but the scale must be clear and justified.

