)
```

Creates a histogram using five intervals.

`edgecolor` adds visible boundaries between bars.

```python
axis.grid(axis="y")
```

Adds grid lines only to the y-axis.

---

### Scatter Plot

```python
axis.scatter(
    data["study_hours"],
    data["exam_score"],
)
```

Uses study hours as x-values and exam scores as y-values.

Each point represents one student.

---

### Sorting Before a Bar Chart

```python
sorted_data = data.sort_values(
    by="exam_score",
    ascending=False,
)
```

Sorts students from highest score to lowest score.

```python
axis.bar(
    sorted_data["student"],
    sorted_data["exam_score"],
)
```

Creates one bar for every student.

```python
axis.set_ylim(0, 100)
```

Sets the y-axis to the valid exam-score range.

```python
axis.tick_params(
    axis="x",
    rotation=45,
)
```

Rotates student names to reduce overlap.

---

### Saving the Chart

```python
figure.savefig(
    output_directory
    / "student_scores.png",
    dpi=300,
    bbox_inches="tight",
)
```

Saves the chart as a high-resolution PNG.

```python
plt.close(figure)
```

Releases memory used by the figure.

This is important when generating many charts.

---

### Creating the Output Directory

```python
output_directory.mkdir(
    parents=True,
    exist_ok=True,
)
```

Creates the output directory.

`parents=True` creates missing parent directories.

`exist_ok=True` avoids an error if the directory already exists.

