## 31. Time Complexity

Let:

* (n) = number of students
* (b) = number of histogram bins

Validation scans the data:

[
O(n)
]

Creating the histogram:

[
O(n + b)
]

Creating each scatter plot:

[
O(n)
]

Sorting students for the bar chart:

[
O(n \log n)
]

Drawing the bar chart:

[
O(n)
]

The sorting operation dominates:

[
\boxed{O(n \log n)}
]

Without sorting, chart creation would be approximately:

[
\boxed{O(n)}
]

The charting library also uses memory for figure objects and graphical elements:

[
\boxed{O(n)}
]

approximately.

