## 39. Summary

* Matplotlib is Python’s foundational visualization library.
* Line charts show change across an ordered sequence.
* Bar charts compare categories.
* Scatter plots show relationships between numerical variables.
* Histograms show numerical distributions.
* Titles and axis labels make charts understandable.
* Legends distinguish multiple plotted series.
* Figure size controls chart dimensions.
* `dpi` controls saved-image resolution.
* The object-oriented interface uses `figure` and `axis`.
* `tight_layout()` reduces overlapping chart elements.
* Visualization helps detect trends, outliers, distributions, and model problems.
* Misleading scales and incorrect chart types can distort conclusions.
* Charts should be generated from validated and cleaned data.

